{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-2327].
  {panel}

*Issue Summary*
Customer would like to be able to Add images next to their welcome page in Service Desk as well as redirect Service Desk to their own customized home when the Help desk button is clicked.

*Step by Step*
- Customer has designed their custom welcome page.
- They would like to either have a link that helps redirect to their custom designed welcome page or edit the existing Help Desk to link to their custom Welcome page.
- Secondly, customer would like to have the ability to add an image to the Welcome Page, however this is different from the icon that is available in {{Service Desk > Project > Setting > Portal Settings}}
-- They want the image to appear only on the Welcome Page right nect to the welcome to signify the product.

h3. Problem Definition
 * Bug described in JSDCLOUD-7959 allows issue types associated with request types to be disassociated with the project/issue type scheme thereby blocking the request type from being able to be deleted

h3. Suggested Solution
 * Add a validator and an error message to state that the request type can't be deleted because of a missing issue type

h3. Why this is important
 * Currently, there isn't an error message in the UI that informs the user that this is the problem. The UI is stuck on this screen without any message or advice:
 !Screenshot 2019-08-21 at 00.09.11.png|thumbnail!

h3. Workaround
 * Open the browser network console and navigate to the "Network" tab. There should be a HTTP 404 response saying:
{noformat}
{
  "errors": [
    {
      "errorMessage": "You can't edit the request type because the issue type it's based on was removed. To restore the request type, add back its associated issue type in this project's issue type scheme."
    }
  ],
  "reasonKey": "sd.error.issuetype.not.associated",
  "reasonCode": "404"
}
{noformat}

h3. *Steps to Reproduce*
 # Go to the SLA settings on a Service Desk project;
 # Edit any SLA;
 # Edit any goal *other than the "All remaining issues"* goal;
 # Click save;
 # A pop-up will appear where you can review the changes

h3. *Expected Results*
 * Only your actual changes are shown.

h3. *Actual Results*
 * *Besides* your actual changes, the All remaining issues calendar will be displayed as the "24/7 Calendar (Default)" calendar:
 ** !wrong_calendar.png|thumbnail!

h3. *Workaround*

There is no workaround. Even though the review will say otherwise, the "All remaining issues" calendar isn't in fact updated.
